Join O'ahu's LGBTQ+ softball league! Whether you're picking up a glove for the first time or you're a seasoned pro, our inclusive community is ready to welcome you.

As proud members of International Pride Softball, we bring together players of all skill levels to enjoy exciting, competitive games in a supportive and fun environment.

Please visit our **Linktree** for all our links and more!

**Season cadence:** We play **every Summer** in Honolulu (Ala Wai Community Park).  
**Tournament cadence:** The league's annual tournament is held the **last weekend in March**.

> Tip: For schedules and standings, see TeamSideline (link in **Official Links**).

title: bylaws
text:
## Definitions
- **ASSL:** Aloha State Softball League
- **Board of Directors:** Governing body of ASSL
- **Commissioner:** Chief executive of ASSL

- **iPride:** International Pride Softball (affiliation)

title: bylaws
text:
## Mission & Purpose
Non-profit, adult community league promoting LGBTQ+ fellowship through softball; safe, inclusive, and free from discrimination.

title: bylaws
text:
## Nonâ€‘Discrimination Policy (summary)
No discrimination based on race, color, ethnicity, national origin, sex, gender identity/expression, sexual orientation, age, religion, disability, marital/family/veteran status, socioeconomic status, political affiliation, or playing ability (except for divisional ratings).

title: bylaws
text:
## Membership
- Open to ages 18+; membership runs Opening Day â†’ day before next Opening Day.
- Requirements: online registration, fee payment, Player Code of Conduct, player rating.
- Categories: **Active Player**, **Nonâ€‘Player** (staff/support), **Honorary Member**.

title: bylaws
text:
## Discipline (summary)
- Team suspension for league debts.
- Member suspension for nonâ€‘payment, physical violence, or unsportsmanlike conduct.
- Physical violence: **automatic 2â€‘game suspension**; second offense in season â†’ **season suspension**.
- Expulsion requires **3/4 Board** vote.

title: bylaws
text:
## Administration
**Board seats (typical):** Commissioner; Assistant Commissioners (C/D/E); Treasurer; Secretary; Partner Orgs & Tournaments; Fields & Equipment; Marketing & Comms; Community Outreach; up to three Membersâ€‘atâ€‘Large.

**Board duties:** vote on codes; approve budget/calendar; consider appeals (suspensions/forfeits); manage operations; interpret codes at games; secure fields; inform league of rule changes.

**Key policies:** member data privacy; 2â€‘year terms; Board meets â‰¥ quarterly; general membership meets â‰¥ twice yearly.

**Precedence:** For governance, bylaws override website copy.

title: ratings
text:
## Method
- **Sunday Scrimmages** (Crane Field, Aprilâ€“May) inform ratings.
- **26â€‘question rubric** across **Hitting (1â€“9)**, **Running Speed (10â€“12)**, **Fielding (13â€“20)**, **Throwing (21â€“26)**.
- **60% rule:** a question is "YES" at â‰¥60% success.

title: ratings
text:
## Placement (YES counts)
- **E:** 0â€“6 YES â€” newer players, developing skills.  
- **D:** 5â€“12 YES â€” intermediate recreational.  
- **C:** 10â€“18 YES â€” experienced recreational.

title: ratings
text:
## Restrictions
- **E:** may **not** hit highâ€‘velocity balls â‰¥20% nor hit fly balls **>300 ft**.  
- **D:** may **not** hit fly balls **>300 ft**.

title: ratings

Short answers pulled from *Gameplay Rules*.

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: How many overâ€‘theâ€‘fence home runs are allowed?
**A:** **C:** 1 per game; **D/E:** 0. *(See: Home Run Limits).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: When does the last inning start?
**A:** No new inning after **50 minutes**. If the clock hits 50:00 and an inning has not started, it cannot begin. *(See: Time & Mercy).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: What's the international tiebreaker?
**A:** The **last batter** from the previous inning starts on **2B**. *(See: Extra Innings).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: What's the extraâ€‘innings pitch format?
**A:** **Oneâ€‘pitch**: **3 balls / 2 strikes**, **no** courtesy fouls (regular season). *(See: Extra Innings).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: Can we use courtesy runners? How often?
**A:** **One per inning**, anyone on the lineup card. *(See: Courtesy Runner).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: How many players can we bat?
**A:** Up to **12** (with up to **2 extra hitters**). *(See: Lineups & Participation).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: Minimum to start?
**A:** **9 players**, 10â€‘minute grace to avoid forfeit. The 10th can join after the current inning ends. *(See: Lineups & Participation).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: Are metal cleats allowed?
**A:** No. *(See: Atâ€‘aâ€‘Glance / Footwear).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: Are USA Softball approved bats required?
**A:** Yes; additionally, **only ASSLâ€‘provided bats** may be used on the field. *(See: Equipment â€” Bats).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: Is base stealing allowed?
**A:** No. *(See: Atâ€‘aâ€‘Glance).*

title: rules-faq
text:
### Q: E Division run rule each inning?
**A:** Max **5 runs/inning** except final atâ€‘bat. *(See: Time & Mercy â€” E Division cap).*

text:

id: rules
title: Gameplay Rules â€” Quick Reference

For onâ€‘field matters, gameplay rules override website copy. USA Softball (ASA) rules apply unless ASSL specifies otherwise.

title: rules
text:
## Atâ€‘aâ€‘Glance
- **Divisions:** C, D, E (no B).  
- **Footwear:** No metal cleats. **Stealing:** not allowed.  
- **Count:** Start **1â€‘1**; one courtesy foul after the second strike.  
- **Pitch arc:** **6â€“12 ft**.  
- **Uniforms:** Likeâ€‘colored shirts/jerseys with visible numbers.

title: rules
text:
## Home Run Limits
- **C:** 1 overâ€‘theâ€‘fence HR per game.  
- **D:** 0.  
- **E:** 0.

title: rules
text:
## Time & Mercy
- **Game clock:** No new inning after **50:00** (Championships may vary by schedule).  
- **Runâ€‘ahead (mercy):** 20 after 3; 15 after 4; 10 after 5â€“6.  
- **E Division cap:** Max **5 runs/inning** (except the final atâ€‘bat).

title: rules
text:
## Lineups & Participation
- Minimum **9** to avoid forfeit (10â€‘minute grace).  
- Teams may bat up to **12**; **2 extra hitters** permitted.  
- The 10th player can join midâ€‘game after the current inning ends.

title: rules
text:
## Courtesy Runner
- **1 per inning**, any player listed on the lineup card.

title: rules
text:
## Extra Innings (Regular Season)
- **Oneâ€‘pitch** format: **3 balls / 2 strikes**, **no** courtesy fouls.  
- **International Tiebreaker:** last batter from the previous inning starts on **2B**.

title: rules
text:
## Championship Games
- Extra innings continue with the standard **1â€‘1** count unless posted otherwise.

title: rules
text:
## Equipment
- **Bats:** Must be on the **USA Softball Approved Bat List**; **only ASSLâ€‘provided bats** may be used on the field.  
- **Ball:** 12â€‘inch pink or yellow optic, **COR â‰¤ .520**, **compression â‰¤ 300 lbs**.

title: rules
text:
## Umpires & Protests
- ASSL assigns/pays umpires; at least one per regularâ€‘season game.  
- Judgment calls are **not** protestable.

title: rules
text:
## Fieldâ€‘Specific â€” Ala Wai Community Park #3
- Boundary lines extend from fence in front of bench areas.  
- **Right field:** to running/bike path. **Left field:** to basketball courts.  
- Fly balls caught beyond those lines are **outs**.  
- Overthrows: **dead ball** + **one base**.  
- Balls striking utility poles/picnic tables or rolling over the rightâ€‘field hill: **groundâ€‘rule double**.

text:

id: scorekeeping
title: Scorekeeping Guide (Slowâ€‘Pitch)
tags: ["scorekeeping", "notation", "positions", "errors", "courtesy runner"]
version: 2025-09-12
---

**You need:** scorebook or notebook, pencil, team lineups.

**Positions (1â€“10):** 1â€‘P, 2â€‘C, 3â€‘1B, 4â€‘2B, 5â€‘3B, 6â€‘SS, 7â€‘LF, 8â€‘CF, 9â€‘RF, 10â€‘Rover (if used).

**Notations:** 1B/2B/3B/HR, BB, K (ê“˜ for looking), F7/F8/F9, 6â€‘3, E5, FC, DP, SAC, HBP, WP, PB.

**Slowâ€‘pitch details:** start 1â€‘andâ€‘1; one foul after 2 strikes = K; no stealing/leading off; mat/plate defines strikes; 6â€“12 ft arc; track courtesy runners and defensive swaps; note mercy rule if invoked.

**Error details (iPrideâ€‘style):** E6(T) throwing error by SS; E4(F) fielding error by 2B; E7(M) misplay by LF.
